<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB06430</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT PROVIDING FOR A REINVESTMENT FRAMEWORK FOR REAL ESTATE INVESTMENT TRUST (REIT) SPONSORS, AMENDING SECTIONS 3, 8, AND 9 OF REPUBLIC ACT NO. 9856, OTHERWISE KNOWN AS "THE REAL ESTATE INVESTMENT TRUST (REIT) ACT OF 2009"</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SHORT TITLE : Providing For A Reinvestment Framework For Real Estate Investment Trust (reit) Sponsors</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Intends to ensure that the funds invested through the "Real Estate Investment Act of 2009" , enacted to promote the development of the capital market to fund infrastructure projects and further improve the real estate industry, are to be reinvested in the Philippines to secure full domestic participation in the real estate industry. Defines the terms "REINVESTMENT PLAN" and provides that any proceeds realized by the sponsor/promoter from the sale of R E I T share or other securities issued in exchange for income - generating real estate transferred to R E I T and any money raised by the sponsor/promoter from the sale of any of its income - generating to the R E I T, in any real estate including any redevelopment thereof, and/or infrastructure projects in the country, must be reinvested in the Philippines.

Mandates that the REIT shall submit a Reinvestment Plan to the Exchange or the Commission upon registration and must annually secure a Certification from the Commission that it is compliant with its Reinvestment Plan.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>GARIN, SHARON S., RODRIGUEZ, RUFUS B., BARBERS, ROBERT ACE S., GATCHALIAN, WESLIE T., AGLIPAY, MICHAEL EDGAR Y., NOGRALES, JERICHO JONAS B.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2020-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>CO-AUTHORS (Journal Entries) :</td></tr><tr><td>1. Cagas (000 2020-05-31)</td><tr><td colspan=3>AUTHORS(Final/Third Reading) :</td></tr><tr><td width='%33'>1. Garin (S.)</td><td width='33%'>2. Rodriguez</td><tr><td width='%33'>3. Barbers</td><td width='33%'>4. Gatchalian</td><tr><td width='%33'>5. Aglipay</td><td width='33%'>6. Nograles (J.J.)</td><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITTEE REPORT NO.&nbsp00250</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED ON 2020-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBMITTED BY:&nbspECONOMIC AFFAIRS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>RECOMMENDATIONS:&nbspApproval in substitution of House Bills Numbered 6163 and 6291</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SUBSTITUTED BILLS:&nbspHB06163, HB06291</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON RULES ON 2020-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE INCLUDED IN OB:&nbsp2020-03-02</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE CALENDARED :&nbsp2020-03-04</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>SECOND READING INFORMATION</b><br /><tr><td colspan=3>PERIOD OF SPONSORSHIP :&nbsp2020-03-04, 2020-03-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SPONSORED BY :&nbsp Garin (S.);Garin (S.)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FINAL LIST OF AUTHORS :&nbspGarin (S.), Rodriguez, Barbers, Gatchalian, Aglipay, Nograles (J.J.)</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE APPROVED ON SECOND READING :&nbsp2020-03-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>THIRD READING INFORMATION</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE COPY DISTRIBUTED TO MEMBERS:&nbsp2020-03-10</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE APPROVED BY THE HOUSE ON THIRD READING :2020-06-01</td></tr><tr><td colspan=